we participated in a medicare health support pilot program through green ribbon health , or grh , a joint- venture company with pfizer health solutions inc .
grh was designed to support cms assigned medicare beneficiaries living with diabetes and/or congestive heart failure in central florida .

grh used disease management initiatives , including evidence-based clinical guidelines , personal self-directed change strategies , and personal nurses to help participants navigate the health system .

revenues under the contract with cms over the period which began november 1 , 2005 and ended august 15 , 2008 are subject to refund unless savings , satisfaction , and clinical improvement targets are met .

to date , all revenues have been deferred until reliable estimates are determinable , and revenues are not expected to be material when recognized .
